# Pull request target repository

When creating pull requests with `gh pr create` in this repo, always target
the fork — not the upstream `grafana/grafana`:

```
gh pr create --repo jgrace19/grafana ...
```

This repo is a fork of `grafana/grafana`. Without `--repo`, `gh` defaults to
opening the PR against the upstream, which is not what we want.
